# GitHub CODEOWNERS for jolliai/jolliai
#
# Combined with the `Require review from Code Owners` branch rule on `main`,
# this file makes the listed teams' approval mandatory for any PR that
# touches the matched paths.
#
# IMPORTANT: GitHub CODEOWNERS uses LAST-matching-pattern-wins (not
# most-specific). Order matters — specific overrides must come AFTER
# broader rules.
#
# Team handles below (`@jolliai/<team>`) point to GitHub Teams. Their
# membership is configured in GitHub org settings, not in this file.

# Default owners — every PR needs at least one maintainer review.
* @jolliai/maintainers

# All CI / release workflows (build + publish). Changes here directly
# affect what code reaches end users — build correctness, publish targets,
# signing/verification logic. Covers any workflow added later, not just the
# publish-* ones currently in the repo.
.github/workflows/  @jolliai/release-team

# Release procedure document (the human counterpart of the workflows).
RELEASE.md  @jolliai/release-team

# Security-sensitive: API key parsing and origin allowlist.
# CLAUDE.md notes "Keep the three implementations in lockstep" —
# any change here implies coordinated changes across CLI / VS Code (via
# bundled CLI helpers) / IntelliJ. Security team review enforces that.
cli/src/core/JolliApiUtils.ts                                @jolliai/security
intellij/src/main/kotlin/ai/jolli/jollimemory/services/      @jolliai/security

# CODEOWNERS itself: modifying *who reviews what* is a governance change,
# distinct from any code change, so it requires admin-level approval.
# Keep this rule LAST so it overrides the `.github/workflows/` rule above
# (last-matching-pattern-wins).
.github/CODEOWNERS  @jolliai/admins
